---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import { site, mailLink, telLandline, telMobile } from '../data/site';

const lastUpdated = '2 June 2026';
const addr = site.address;
const postal = `${site.name}, ${addr.unit}, ${addr.estate}, ${addr.street}, ${addr.area}, ${addr.city}, ${addr.region} ${addr.postcode}`;
---

<Layout
  current="/privacy-policy"
  title="Privacy Policy | Major Car Parts"
  description="How Major Car Parts collects, uses and protects your personal data under UK GDPR. Your rights and how to contact us."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Privacy Policy"
    subtitle="How we handle your personal data."
    crumb="Privacy Policy"
  />

  <section class="py-20 md:py-28 bg-white">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="legal-prose fade-in">
        <p class="text-muted-light text-[0.85rem] uppercase tracking-[0.16em] font-mono mb-8">
          Last updated: {lastUpdated}
        </p>

        <p>
          This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>{site.name}</strong> (&ldquo;we&rdquo;,
          &ldquo;us&rdquo; or &ldquo;our&rdquo;) collects, uses, shares and protects your
          personal data when you contact us, request a quote, buy parts or use our fitting,
          body repair and spray paint services. We are committed to handling your information
          responsibly and in line with the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and
          the Data Protection Act 2018.
        </p>
        <p>
          Please note this website is a demonstration site. The business details below are
          genuine, but some online features (such as forms) may direct you to contact us by
          phone, WhatsApp or email rather than submitting data through the site.
        </p>

        <h2>Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          For the purposes of data protection law, <strong>{site.name}</strong> is the data
          controller responsible for your personal data. You can reach us using the details
          below:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Business:</strong> {site.name}</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Address:</strong> {addr.unit}, {addr.estate}, {addr.street},
            {addr.area}, {addr.city}, {addr.region} {addr.postcode}
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Email:</strong> <a href={mailLink}>{site.email}</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Landline:</strong> <a href={telLandline}>{site.phoneLandline}</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Mobile / WhatsApp:</strong> <a href={telMobile}>{site.phoneMobile}</a>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this policy or how we use your personal data, please
          contact us using any of the methods above.
        </p>

        <h2>What information we collect</h2>
        <p>
          We only collect the information we need to respond to you and to supply the parts and
          services you ask for. Depending on how you get in touch, this may include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Your contact details</strong> - your name, telephone number and email
            address, so we can reply to your enquiry and keep you updated.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Vehicle details</strong> - information such as the make, model, year,
            registration or VIN of your vehicle, so we can identify the correct parts or
            quote for fitting, body repair or spray paint work.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>The content of your enquiry</strong> - the message, photographs or part
            details you send us by email, WhatsApp, phone or any quote request, including
            anything you choose to tell us about the work you need.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Delivery and order details</strong> - where you purchase parts, the
            address, items and any reference information needed to fulfil and dispatch your
            order.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Basic website analytics</strong> - where you have given consent, limited
            information about how you use this website (such as the pages you view and your
            approximate region), collected through cookies. See <a href="/cookie-policy">our
            Cookie Policy</a> for details.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not intentionally collect any special category data (such as health
          information) and we ask that you do not send us such information. We do not knowingly
          collect data from children.
        </p>

        <h2>How we use it &amp; lawful basis</h2>
        <p>
          We use your personal data only for clear, legitimate purposes, and we always have a
          lawful basis under the UK GDPR for doing so:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>To respond to your enquiries and provide quotes</strong> - answering your
            questions about parts availability, pricing, fitting, body repair and spray paint.
            Lawful basis: our <strong>legitimate interests</strong> in responding to and
            helping potential and existing customers, and/or taking <strong>steps at your
            request prior to entering into a contract</strong>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>To supply parts and carry out work</strong> - sourcing, ordering, fitting,
            repairing, refinishing, delivering and invoicing. Lawful basis:
            <strong>performance of a contract</strong> with you, or steps taken at your request
            before entering into one.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>To keep proper business records</strong> - for accounting, tax, warranty
            and dispute-resolution purposes. Lawful basis: compliance with a
            <strong>legal obligation</strong> and our legitimate interests in running the
            business properly.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>To improve and secure our website</strong> - using analytics and similar
            technologies. Lawful basis: your <strong>consent</strong>, which you can give or
            withdraw at any time through our cookie controls.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not use your personal data for automated decision-making that produces legal or
          similarly significant effects, and we will not send you marketing communications
          unless you have asked us to or otherwise agreed to receive them.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          Our website uses a small number of cookies. Essential cookies help the site work and
          remember your preferences; optional analytics cookies are only set if you consent.
          You can manage your choices at any time. For full details of the cookies we use and
          how to control them, please see our <a href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>Sharing your information</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>We do not sell your personal data, and we never share it for third-party
          marketing.</strong> We only share information where it is necessary to provide our
          parts and services, or where we are required to by law. This may include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Delivery and courier providers</strong> - to dispatch parts to you, where
            relevant.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Payment providers</strong> - to process payments securely. We do not store
            full card details ourselves.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Suppliers and manufacturers</strong> - only where needed to source a
            specific part or honour a warranty.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Professional advisers and authorities</strong> - such as our accountants,
            or HMRC and other bodies, where we are legally required to disclose information.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Where we use service providers, we only share the minimum information needed and
          expect them to keep your data secure and use it solely for the purpose we have
          engaged them for.
        </p>

        <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
        <p>
          We keep your personal data only for as long as we need it for the purposes set out in
          this policy:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>General enquiries</strong> that do not lead to an order are typically kept
            for a short period and then deleted or anonymised.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Order, sales and service records</strong> are kept for as long as required
            to meet our legal, accounting, tax and warranty obligations, generally for several
            years after the work or sale is complete.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          When we no longer need your personal data, we will securely delete or anonymise it.
        </p>

        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          Under the UK GDPR you have a number of rights over your personal data. You have the
          right to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Access</strong> - request a copy of the personal data we hold about you.</li>
          <li><strong>Rectification</strong> - ask us to correct data that is inaccurate or incomplete.</li>
          <li><strong>Erasure</strong> - ask us to delete your personal data in certain circumstances.</li>
          <li><strong>Restriction</strong> - ask us to limit how we use your data in certain circumstances.</li>
          <li><strong>Objection</strong> - object to our processing of your data based on legitimate interests.</li>
          <li><strong>Portability</strong> - request that certain data be transferred to you or another provider.</li>
          <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> - where we rely on your consent, withdraw it at any time (this does not affect processing already carried out).</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the details in the
          <a href="#contact-us">&ldquo;Contact us&rdquo;</a> section below. We will respond
          within the timeframes required by law and there is normally no charge.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you are unhappy with how we have handled your personal data, you have the right to
          complain to the Information Commissioner&rsquo;s Office (ICO), the UK&rsquo;s data
          protection regulator. You can contact the ICO at
          <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk</a>. We would,
          however, appreciate the chance to address your concerns first, so please do consider
          contacting us before approaching the ICO.
        </p>

        <h2>Data security</h2>
        <p>
          We take appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect your personal
          data against loss, misuse, unauthorised access, disclosure or alteration. Access to
          the information you share with us is limited to those who need it to deal with your
          enquiry or order. While no method of transmission or storage is ever completely
          secure, we work to keep your data safe and to deal promptly with any issues that
          arise.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our
          practices, our services or the law. Any changes will be posted on this page with a
          revised &ldquo;last updated&rdquo; date. We encourage you to review this page
          periodically. This policy was last updated on <strong>{lastUpdated}</strong>.
        </p>

        <h2 id="contact-us">Contact us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, wish to exercise your rights, or
          want to raise a concern about how we handle your personal data, please get in touch:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href={mailLink}>{site.email}</a></li>
          <li><strong>Landline:</strong> <a href={telLandline}>{site.phoneLandline}</a></li>
          <li><strong>Mobile / WhatsApp:</strong> <a href={telMobile}>{site.phoneMobile}</a></li>
          <li><strong>Post:</strong> {postal}</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
